   <descr>
      <p>"Roses Are Red (My Love)" is a popular song composed by Al
    Byron and Paul Evans. It was recorded by Bobby Vinton and was a
    number-one song in the United States during the year 1962. It
    topped the Billboard Hot 100 singles chart on July 15, 1962,
    and remained there for four weeks. The recording was his first
    hit. He found the song in a reject pile at Epic Records. He
    first recorded it as an R&amp;B number but was allowed to
    record it with a new arrangement including strings. The single
    was also the first number one hit for Epic.</p>
